## [Your First Swift App](https://leanpub.com/yourfirstswiftapp/)



An introduction building iOS apps Swift, third edition book originally kickstarted 2013. introduces readers fundamental concepts building first iOS application, process building _my_ first app.

From first Xcode project App Store submission process, book covers tasks common iOS application, table views, user interaction, even Core Data. book instructs readers _process_ development, not specific syntax APIs. gives readers tools need continue learn grow towards becoming accomplished iOS developers.

 

## [UICollectionView: Complete Guide](http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B00IHZKDCU/ref=as_li_tl?ie=UTF8&camp=1789&creative=390957&creativeASIN=B00IHZKDCU&linkCode=as2&tag=ashfur-20&linkId=GUX5WHOORCNFA32C)



I’ve worked Addison-Wesley publish two editions book date, describe complete detail effectively use collection views iOS applications build unique, immersive experiences. Unlike technical books, mine covers _and_ why using technology. [More details available](/uicollectionview-the-complete-guide/).

 

## [Functional Reactive Programming iOS (Retired)](https://leanpub.com/iosfrp)



Functional reactive programming declarative programming paradigm used simplify complex, asynchronous tasks. read history FRP, its philosophy [ReactiveCocoa website](http://reactivecocoa.io/philosophy.html).

In book, introduce readers ReactiveCocoa, FRP framework Objective-C. book first covers philosophy functional programming, guides readers real code examples. ReactiveCocoa used remainder book guides readers implementing real-world use FRP. Finally, discuss Model View ViewModel, structure code FRP increases testability code reuse.

**Note**: book relied 500px API, [shut down June 2018](https://support.500px.com/hc/en-us/articles/360002435653-API-). retired book officially. you're interested functional reactive programming, check [this book contributed Ray Wenderlich](https://store.raywenderlich.com/products/rxswift).

 

Other works include earlier editions _Your First Swift App_ titled [Your First iOS App](https://leanpub.com/your-first-ios-app), [Beginning Objective-C](http://amzn.to/1QbzZtc) co-authored Jim Dovey.

In addition writing books iOS developers, provide technical review books. I’ve collaborated following books:

- [Reactive Programming Swift](https://store.raywenderlich.com/products/rxswift)
- [Swift Really Impatient](http://amzn.to/1V1U57p)
- [Build iOS Games Sprite Kit](http://amzn.to/1gBpAr0)
- [Learning Core Data iOS Swift](http://amzn.to/1Ne1C1t)
